title: For Sale:  M1 Carbine - real USGI - updated info
postcontent:
Selling a very nice USGI M1 Carbine. It is a national postal meter (NPM). It comes with a NPM USGI 15-round magazine marked UN and the sling and oiler. It has no import marks. Bought from CMP and is a service grade.

I have had a couple questions and am providing all answers here for those of you contemplating buying this very nice piece of America's military history.

The barrel is an Underwood.  NPM did not make their own barrels and was part of the free barrel program. The stock and hand guard are birch, and I can't find any maker marks or rebuild marks. Other major parts are:
Trigger housing: Inland
Bolt: Inland
Slide: Inland

It seems to be your standard USGI carbine that has been updated and/or rebuilt during the 70 plus years since it was built and used in WWII.

I will provide the original CMP certificate of authenticity to the buyer. I do have extra ammo and 15- and 30-round magazines I would sell with the rifle at a reasonble price.  I am not currently considering lower offers since I just listed today, if it doesn't sell in a few days, I may consider lower offers.

Again, thanks for lookiing and I will only sell face to face and will not ship.

location: Salisbury, Rockwell, Granite Quarry, Faith, North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
I have a Keltec P11 9mm double action only.  Comes with two 10 round factory magazines.  Comes with the Keltec frame mounted carry clip in Stainless Steel.  Right hand carry for the clip position.  Also comes with the factory hard case and manual.

I have completely worked this gun over with the full fluff-n-buff job on the barrel, frame, and trigger.  I have reshaped the feed ramp by removing the factory hump which tends to drag on 147 grain ammo and polished it to a full shine.  I beveled the mag well, and removed all the molding flash on the grip and frame.  Trigger registers right around 7 lbs, down from the factory 11, and is very smooth and non-stacking.  (I added an over travel trigger stop behind the trigger that is instantly removed.  It is covered by grip tape in the picture.  It cut my group size by more than half.)  I made the slide lock much easier to release by filing and polishing the necessary areas.  I polished the magazine followers and polished the internals of the magazines and springs for even more reliable function.  I have carried this gun many times and it has always worked flawlessly after I put some elbow grease and loving care into it.  It does have a few tiny light scratches on the slide from being carried, but this gun isn't about being a mantle piece.  It's a save your ass gun that needs to work!

You get a good, ready to carry firearm made great, with all of the hard reliability upgrade work already done!

Buyer must have handgun purchase permit or concealed handgun permit.  Must be willing to sign a bill of sale.  

$400 cash.  Negotiable with trades.
